-- Unipetrol Declines on Report Czech Minister Is Mulling New Tax
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-04-17T09:40:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/unipetrol-declines-on-report-czech-minister-is-mulling-new-tax.html
Unipetrol AS (UNIP) , the biggest Czech oil
refiner, declined after E15 newspaper reported that Industry and
Trade Minister Martin Kuba proposed a new tax on motor fuels.  The stock slipped 1.7 percent, the most since April 6, to
170.11 koruna by 11:29 a.m. in Prague. The 14-member  PX (PX)  index,
where Unipetrol has a 4.2 percent weighting, slid 0.6 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  